race.comment: Tricky and the betting moves will be instructive. Hayes-trained NEVERENOUGHLEGO (5) showed good ability his only two starts last preparation and resumed with a 2.2L defeat here over 1000m. He has plenty to give and will be fitter. The longer sprint suits as does this assignment. TEXTURE (10) debuts and the stable flies at home. Looked good in both the recent Flemington jumpouts and draws the inside barrier. JUSTIBELLA (13) ran second in her latest trial at Cranbourne. Early signs certainly encouraging. ORNITHOLOGY (7) debuts off a Flemington trial win. Half brother to Group 1 winner Reserve Bank.
